A blasting operation will take place at the Hammarsdale Interchange on the N3 on Tuesday at about 3pm. A statement from South African Roads Agency Limited (Sanral) says both carriageways of the N3 between the Cato Ridge and Peacevale interchanges will be closed between 3pm and 4pm.However, the time may need to be adjusted depending on weather conditions on the day. Traffic will be diverted to the R103 at Shongweni and Cato Ridge interchanges.“Due to the close proximity of the blast site to Meadway Road and MR385, it will be necessary to close Meadway Road and MR385 in the vicinity of the Hammarsdale interchange during the blast operation,” read the statementTraffic on Meadway Road would be diverted via Thousand Hills Drive, said Sanral.However, steps will be taken to ensure that the roads are closed for the shortest possible time.The roads agency urged motorists to drive carefully and adhere to the speed limits.